import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='lon', y='lat', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude coordinates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    capital_cities = data.groupby('state')['city'].count().reset_index()
    capital_cities = capital_cities.rename(columns={'city': 'number_of_capital_cities'})
    capital_cities = capital_cities.sort_values(by='number_of_capital_cities', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='number_of_capital_cities', data=capital_cities)
    chart.axhline(y=capital_cities['number_of_capital_cities'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max number of capital cities')
    chart.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.spatial.distance import pdist, squareform

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the distance matrix between the capital cities
    coords = data[['lat', 'lon']].values
    dist_matrix = squareform(pdist(coords))

    # Create a heatmap of the distance matrix
    sns.heatmap(dist_matrix, cmap='YlGnBu', square=True, xticklabels=data['city'], yticklabels=data['city'])

    # Set chart title
    plt.title('What is the average distance between the capital cities?')

    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lon', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['lon'].mean(), color='red', label=f"Mean: {data['lon'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of capital cities by longitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lat', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['lat'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of capital cities by latitude?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
